title: Former students of Central School, 1942
description: Transcribed from front of photograph: "Seattle Portraits. Group. Former students of Central School (first) participating in ceremony of putting commemorative plate on corner of Third and Madison 1942." Transcribed from back of photograph: “In 1942 a commemorative plate was placed on the building now occupying the site of the original Central School, at Third and Madison.  Among those participating in the exercises were former students shown in the above photograph.  1-Charles Kinnear  2-Harry Jacobs  3-Frank Atkins  4-William Coffman  5-Frank McRea  6-Loleta Hammond Harkins  7-Florence Stowell (Hubbart)  8-Blake D. Mills  9-Edith Randolph Warner  10-Frankie Whaley Nemeyer  11-Katherine Whitworth Schultz  12-Alfred Schillestad  13-Rollie Andrews  14-Clara Hinkley Moran  15-Allie Bartholomew Blumberg  16-Margaret Yarno  17-Charles Thorndike  18- Mamie Coffman Dawson  19-(back of 18) Clara Wilson  20-Ida Marshall Andrus  21-James Hubbart”

description: Transcribed from front of photograph: "Seattle Portraits. Russel, Sarah Jane Gallagher, b. 1855. Second wife of Thomas S. Russel. One of the "Mercer girls."" Transcribed from back of photograph: “MRS. THOMAS RUSSELL - one of the “Mercer Girls”, who married Thomas Russell, early-day pioneer, taught the public grammar school in Yesler's Pavilion, 1869-1870. She also conducted private school and classes in music. A son, George Russell was once Seattle postmaster.”
